{"word":"Samaria","slug":"samaria","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Samaria</b> <a href=\"#/H8111\">H8111</a><br/><a href=\"#/H8115\">H8115</a> <br/> 1. City of:<br/> - Built by Omri<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=16&verse=24'>1Ki 16:24</a> <br/> - Capital of the kingdom of the ten tribes<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=16&verse=29'>1Ki 16:29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=22&verse=51'>1Ki 22:51</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=13&verse=1'>2Ki 13:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=13&verse=10'>2Ki 13:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=15&verse=8'>2Ki 15:8</a> <br/> - Besieged by Ben-Hadad<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=20'>1Ki 20</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=6&verse=33'>2Ki 6:33</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=7'>2Ki 7</a> <br/> - The king of Syria is led into, by Elisha, who miraculously blinds him and his army<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=6&verse=23'>2Ki 6:23</a> <br/> - Ahab ruled in<br/> <a href='S:Ahab'>Ahab</a>; <a href='S:Jezebel'>Jezebel</a> <br/> - Besieged by Shalmaneser, king of Assyria, three years; taken; the people carried away to Halah and Habor, cities of the Medes<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=6'>2Ki 17:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=18&verse=11'>2Ki 18:11</a> <br/> - Idolatry of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=16&verse=32'>1Ki 16:32</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=13&verse=6'>2Ki 13:6</a> <br/> - Temple of, destroyed<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=10&verse=28'>2Ki 10:28</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=23&verse=19'>2Ki 23:19</a> <br/> - Paul and Barnabas preach in<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=15&verse=3'>Act 15:3</a> <br/> - Visited by Philip, Peter, and John<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=8&verse=25'>Act 8:25</a> <br/> 2. Country of:<br/> - General references<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=7&verse=9'>Isa 7:9</a> <br/> - Foreign colonies distributed among the cities of, by the king of Assyria<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=41'>2Ki 17:41</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=15&chapter=4&verse=10'>Ezr 4:10</a> <br/> - Roads through, from Judea into Galilee<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=17&verse=11'>Luk 17:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=4&verse=8'>Joh 4:8</a> <br/> - Jesus journeys through<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=4&verse=42'>Joh 4:42</a> <br/> - Jesus heals lepers in<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=17&verse=19'>Luk 17:19</a> <br/> - The good Samaritan from<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=10&verse=35'>Luk 10:35</a> <br/> No dealings between the Jews and the inhabitants of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=4&verse=9'>Joh 4:9</a><br/> - Expect the Messiah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=4&verse=25'>Joh 4:25</a> <br/> - Disciples made from the inhabitants of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=4&verse=42'>Joh 4:42</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=8&verse=8'>Act 8:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=8&verse=17'>Act 8:17</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=8&verse=25'>Act 8:25</a> <br/> - Jesus forbids the apostles to preach in the cities of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=10&verse=5'>Mat 10:5</a> "}]}